# 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 YANG Module Architecture Block Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    A[YANG MODULE FILE .yang] --> B[YANG COMPILER yanglint pyang]
    B --> C[VALIDATED SCHEMA TREE]
    C --> D{NETCONF OR RESTCONF}
    D -- NETCONF --> E[XML SERIALIZATION]
    D -- RESTCONF --> F[JSON SERIALIZATION]
    E --> G[NETCONF CLIENT]
    F --> H[HTTP CLIENT]
    G --> I[IoT DEVICE NETCONF SERVER]
    H --> I
    I -- state data --> J[YANG NOTIFICATIONS]
    I -- config data --> K[DEVICE HARDWARE]
    J --> C
    K --> I
```

## 4.2 YANG Node Tree Structure for IoT Sensor Module

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    M[MODULE iot-temperature-sensor] --> T[TYPEDEF temperature-celsius]
    M --> G[GROUPING sensor-identity]
    G --> G1[LEAF id uint32 mandatory]
    G --> G2[LEAF location string]
    M --> C1[CONTAINER sensors]
    C1 --> L1[LIST sensor keyed by id]
    L1 --> U1[USES sensor-identity]
    L1 --> LF1[LEAF enabled boolean default true]
    L1 --> LF2[LEAF last-reading config false]
    L1 --> LF3[LEAF last-updated yang date and time]
    L1 --> CH[CHOICE power-source]
    CH --> CA1[CASE battery]
    CA1 --> LB1[LEAF battery-level uint8]
    CH --> CA2[CASE mains]
    CA2 --> LB2[LEAF mains-voltage decimal64]
    L1 --> MS[MUST constraint]
    M --> R[RPC reset-sensor]
    R --> IN[INPUT target-sensor-id leafref]
    R --> OUT[OUTPUT reset-status reset-timestamp]
    M --> N[NOTIFICATION temperature-threshold-alert]
    M --> AU[AUGMENT if interfaces interface]
    AU --> SB[LEAF sensor-binding leafref]
```

## 4.3 YANG Statement Resolution Lifecycle

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    S1[STEP 1 Parse Module] --> S2[STEP 2 Resolve Imports]
    S2 --> S3[STEP 3 Build Symbol Table]
    S3 --> S4[STEP 4 Validate Types]
    S4 --> S5[STEP 5 Apply Substatements]
    S5 --> S6[STEP 6 Resolve XPath Leafrefs]
    S6 --> S7[STEP 7 Generate Tree Schema]
    S7 --> S8[STEP 8 Produce XML or JSON Instance]
```

## 4.4 YANG Data Path Resolution Example

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[CLIENT QUERY /sensors/sensor id=1/last-reading] --> B[RESOLVE NAMESPACE temp-sensor]
    B --> C[NAVIGATE TO CONTAINER sensors]
    C --> D[NAVIGATE TO LIST sensor]
    D --> E[FILTER BY KEY id=1]
    E --> F[NAVIGATE TO LEAF last-reading]
    F --> G[RETURN VALUE 22.50]
    G --> H[WRAP IN rpc-reply XML or JSON]
```

## 4.5 Relationship Between YANG, NETCONF, and IoT Stack

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph APP_LAYER[APPLICATION LAYER]
        A1[IoT Controller Dashboard]
        A2[Analytics Engine]
    end
    subgraph MANAGEMENT_LAYER[MANAGEMENT LAYER]
        B1[NETCONF or RESTCONF Client]
        B2[YANG Schema Library]
    end
    subgraph DEVICE_LAYER[IoT DEVICE LAYER]
        C1[NETCONF Server]
        C2[YANG Modules for each capability]
        C3[Sensor Actuator Hardware]
    end
    APP_LAYER --> MANAGEMENT_LAYER
    MANAGEMENT_LAYER -- SSH or HTTPS --> DEVICE_LAYER
    C1 --> C2
    C1 --> C3
```
